GE2 is a quip. The menu text is "'How's business?'". The display text is "[first time]'So how's business, Germaise?' you ask.[paragraph break]Germaise sighs. 'I've had the ovens fired up night and day all week trying to fill a rush order for Baron Fossville. It's good for business, don't get me wrong, but...' He slaps dispiritedly at the dough, sending up a puff of flour. 'You have to spend [i]time[r] on a pastry to make it just right. Breaks my heart to do slapdash work like this, but what can you do? The Baron wants quantity, not quality.'[subsequently][rp] 'just trying to get all these pastries done before tomorrow night.'[only]"

GE3 is a quip. The menu text is "'What have you got to sell today?'". The display text is "[first time]Knowing that the question always puts him in a good mood, you ask, 'What are you selling today, Germaise?'[paragraph break]A smile spreads across the baker's flour-streaked face. 'What is it you desire?' he replies. 'I have round breads and flat breads, grain breads and white breads, hard breads and soft breads, long loaves and demi-loaves. I make rolls, muffins, pastries, cakes, and the most delicious fried dough you will ever taste. It is no joke to say that my buns are the most firm and delicious in all of Toresal.'[subsequently][rp] 'I have every kind of bread and pastry you could imagine.'[only]"

GE4 is a quip. The menu text is "'Do you know about the mercenaries in Grubber's Market?'". The display text is "[first time]'So...' you say, trying to play it tricky, 'you hear anything about mercenaries running around Grubber's?'[paragraph break]'Eh?' Germaise looks up, startled. 'Mercenaries in Grubber's?'[paragraph break]'Oh yeah,' you say. 'I, uh, heard they were kicking over stalls, scaring the locals, really roughing up the place. I was just wondering if you knew anything about it?'[paragraph break]'Did they knock over Teisha's tent?' Germaise blurts out. 'Is Teisha all right?'[subsequently]'I only know what I heard from you,' says Germaise.[only]"

GE5 is a quip. The menu text is "'Have you seen Bobby around?'". The display text is "[first time]'You seen Bobby around lately?'[paragraph break]'Seen him?' Germaise snaps. 'I chased him out of here for stealing one of my tarts! You tell him from me, he comes around my bakery again, he gets the wrong end of my bread knife in his you-know-what!'[paragraph break]'So... that'd be a [i]no[r], then?'[paragraph break]Germaise sniffs and pounds at his dough.[subsequently][rp] 'I haven't seen him, and that's a good thing.'[only]"

GE6 is a quip. The menu text is "'Nothing, never mind.'" The display text is "'Oh, nothing,' you say.[paragraph break]Germaise nods and goes back to his dough."

GE7 is a quip. The menu text is "'What's the occasion for the pastries?'" The display text is "[first time]'So what are all the pastries for?' you ask. Somehow, you never envisioned Fossville as someone who was particularly passionate about eating pastries.[paragraph break]Germaise shrugs. 'Fossville should tell me his business? Maybe he just likes pastries. Maybe he's throwing a big party. All the more reason to take extra care over the pastries if that's the case, but what do I know? I'm just the baker.'[subsequently][rp] 'I don't know why he wants all the pastries. I suppose he's entertaining someone.'[only]"

GE8 is a quip. The menu text is "'What do you think of Baron Fossville?'" The display text is "[first time]'What do you think of Baron Fossville?' you ask. 'It sounds like you're not exactly pleased to be getting his custom.'[paragraph break]'No, no, it's not that, not that at all,' Germaise says hastily. 'Fossville runs the city well and his taxes are fair. They say he has a temper, but who am I to judge? Now, the Duke before him...' he seems on the verge of saying something, but then thinks better of it. 'Eh, well,' he mutters, and attacks his dough with renewed vigor.[subsequently][rp] 'he's no worse than most.'[only]"

GE9 is a quip. The menu text is "'What do you think of the Queen?'". The display text is "[first time]'What do you think of the Queen?' you ask.[paragraph break]Germaise shrugs and makes a dismissive [i]pfff[r] noise, blowing a cloud of flour from his moustache. 'I try not to. The King placed a greater value on looks than wisdom, and that is his royal prerogative, but then he went and died and the rest of us had to live with the consequences.'[subsequently][rp] 'she's a poor ruler at best, a Royal fool at worst.'[only]"

GE10 is a quip. The menu text is "'What do you think of the Princess?'". The display text is "[first time]'What do you think of the Princess?' you ask.[paragraph break]Germaise shrugs. 'I hear she's a pretty thing, like her mother once was. That plus the throne makes her quite the prize.'[subsequently][rp] 'I don't know much about her.'[only]"

GE11 is a quip. The menu text is "'What do you know about the Ascension?'".
The display text is "[first time]'It seems like the Ascension is all anyone talks about lately,' you say. 'What's the big deal, anyway?'[paragraph break]Germaise rolls his eyes and flaps his flour-white hands in the air. 'Eh, a big how-do-you-do about nothing, believe me. The Ascension is when the throne is bestowed on the Queen's successor. Officially we common folk get some say in who that will be, but if you believe that, you're daft. Anyone with a dram of sense knows that the throne will go to the Queen's daughter, and to whoever is ruthless enough and lucky enough to wed her. Don't trouble your head about Royal politics, Jack,' Germaise adds, giving his dough a vicious punch. 'It's far above the likes of you and me.'[subsequently][rp] 'it's no use worrying about Royal politics; it's nothing to do with the lives of common folk.'[only]"

GE12 is a quip. The menu text is "'What did you think of the old Duke?'". The display text is "[first time]'It's only been a couple of years since the old Duke died,' you say. 'Do you miss him?'[paragraph break]Germaise gets a faraway look in his eyes. 'Ah, Duke Toresal,' he mutters, 'there was a bright and honorable Lord. He'd have been in line for the throne himself if he hadn't married below his station. And if he hadn't died.' He sighs. 'Eh, well. Those were better days, Jack.'[subsequently][rp] 'he was a good man who died before his time.'[only]"

GE13 is a quip. The menu text is "'Yes, Teisha's fine.'". The display text is "[i]There he goes again[r], you think, trying not to roll your eyes too obviously. 'Yeah, uh, Teisha's just fine. She's great.'[paragraph break]Germaise lets out a sigh of relief. 'Ah good. Such a lovely girl, that Teisha. Such a [i]firm[r] girl. Maybe I'll send her a few pastries as a gift, so she knows I'm thinking about her...'"

GE14 is a quip. The menu text is "'The mercenaries roughed Teisha up.'". The display text is "'No, actually, the mercenaries roughed her up and stomped all over her tent,' you say, relishing the effect that this news has on Germaise, who has had a crush on your friend for as long as you can remember.[paragraph break]'The scoundrels!' Germaise shouts, slamming his fist into the middle of his mound of dough with a dull [i]splat[r]. 'I'll go see her right away, I'll bring her a plate of my best pastries. I'll, uh...' he looks around in dismay. 'I'll do that... as soon as I finish the Baron's order.' He starts working the dough at double-speed."

GE15 is a quip. The menu text is "'One more question.'". The display text is "'You mind if I ask you something else?' you ask.[paragraph break]'As long as it doesn't slow down my pastries,' Germaise replies."

