FI10 is a quip. The display text is "Fiona sighs. 'Now, Jacqueline, you know the curfew rules here. You can stay out all night if you like — although I wish you wouldn't — but once you're in and the evening bells ring, you're in. And I can't let you out after Widow Theresa's locked the doors for the night; it would undermine her authority.'[paragraph break]All you can do is seethe. Just for once, it would be nice if the things Widow Theresa says about Fiona playing favorites with you were actually [i]true[r]."

