Section 3 - Jacobs's Conversation 

JA1 is a quip. The display text is "He doesn't answer you at all; he just keeps staring with those creepy, bloodshot eyes."

JA2 is a quip. The display text is "Suddenly the shadowy man in the corner puts his huge, thick-fingered hands on his knees and pushes himself up. 'Well,' he grunts in a thick, rough voice, 'now that the guards are busy takin care of [i]him[r]...' the man stretches, glances at you, and smiles. It is not a friendly smile.[paragraph break]'Hi, kid. Name's Jacobs.'"

JA3 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'My name's Jack.'". The display text is "'Um... hi,' you manage to say. 'My name's, uh… Jack.'"
The following quip is JA5.

JA4 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'Stay away from me!'". The display text is "Without meaning to, you find yourself backing into the far corner of the cell. 'Stay away from me,' you say, trying to sound brave. 'I have... I have powerful friends!'"
The following quip is JA5.

JA5 is a quip. The display text is "The man named Jacobs glances at you, a flicker of amusement crossing his dull, reddish eyes, but doesn't otherwise respond."

JA6 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'Do you know any way to get out of here?'". The display text is "'Do you, uh...,' you clear your throat, '...do you know some way we could get out of this place?'[paragraph break]Jacobs raises an eyebrow. 'Well now, little runt. I suppose I do.'"
The following quip is JA7.

JA7 is a quip. The display text is "The hulking man walks over to the cell door and squints at it for a while, standing with his hands on his hips. 'My father'll have me out of here by tomorrow, of course,' he mutters, 'but I don't like to wait that long.' He barely looks at you — in fact, you're not sure that he's talking [i]to[r] you at all. It's more like he's just muttering to himself.[paragraph break]He bends over and digs something out of the side of his boot, then stands up and thrusts his hand through the viewing window. He curses and strains to push his arm through, but the bars are too narrowly spaced — he can't reach out past his elbow. 'Damn,' he mutters, 'didn't expect this...'"

JA8 is a quip. The display text is "'[i]Aaah![no line break][r] Goddesses curse it!' Jacobs jerks his hand back, rubbing his wrist.[paragraph break]'Well, you gonna help me, runt, or not?' he asks, and holds out a short, stiff piece of wire, pinched between his thumb and forefinger."

JA9 is a quip. The menu text is "'What is that thing?'". The display text is "'What is that thing?' you ask, squinting at the tiny wire — although you're pretty sure you already know.[paragraph break]'What are you, dim?' snarls Jacobs. 'It's a lockpick. Now take it and help me get this door open.'"

JA10 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'I'd rather not.'". The display text is "Picking locks has never been your strong suit, and the idea of this brute breathing over your shoulder while you try it gives you stomach-flips. 'Uh-uh,' you say, holding up your hands and backing away. 'I'd rather not, if it's all the same.'"
The following quip is JA11.

JA11 is a quip. The display text is "'Oh, for the love of — [i]fine![no line break][r]' he yells. He throws the lockpick to the floor and stomps back to his corner. 'I guess I'll just wait for my father, then. A hundred cells in this twice-cursed jail, and I get stuck in the one with a dim-witted, muling runt and a tiny window...'"

JA12 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'Okay.'". The display text is "'Um, okay,' you say, and pluck the wire from his thick, calloused fingers."
The following quip is JA13.

JA13 is a quip. The display text is "'That's the spirit, runt!' Jacobs says. Suddenly he comes over and puts his huge hands around your waist, hoisting you up as though you weighed no more than a sack of feathers. He feels strong enough to snap you in half.[paragraph break]'You ever pick a lock before, runt?'"

JA14 is a quip. The menu text is "'Yes.'". The display text is "You manage a nod. It's [i]sort of[r] true... Bobby showed you a few tricks once, and you've practiced on an old padlock. But you've never tried to pick an actual working lock on an actual door before.[paragraph break]'Good,' Jacob says, pushing you up against the viewing window. 'This one should be easy, long as you can reach it.'"

JA15 is a quip. The menu text is "'No.'". The display text is "'No,' you lie.[paragraph break]'Well, doesn't matter,' Jacobs mutters, pushing you up against the viewing window. 'These jail locks aren't complicated. Just reach down there and jiggle around a bit.'"

JA16 is a quip. The display text is "Jacobs turns to you. 'I heard what your friend in the other cell said, before they dragged him out,' he says. 'Sounds like Fossville's taken quite an interest in you.'"

JA17 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'Yes, he has.'". The display text is "You nod. 'I guess he has,' you say, 'but I have no idea why.'"
The following quip is JA19.

JA18 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'I don't know what you're talking about.'". The display text is "Something tells you not to trust this man. 'I don’t know what you're talking about,' you say, trying to sound tough and sullen. 'I don't know what [i]he[r] was talking about, either. Why would Fossville be interested in me?'[paragraph break]Jacobs gives you a shrewd look. You're not sure if he believes you or not."
The following quip is JA19.

JA19 is a quip. The display text is "The big man seems to consider something. 'You can come with me if you want,' he says. 'I'll take you somewhere safe.'[paragraph break]A shaky, wheedling voice from the north cell calls out: 'Don't you listen to him, girl! That's Jacobs the Elder's son; he'd as soon sell you to slavers as help you.'[paragraph break][i]'Shut up, you!'[no line break][r] yells Jacobs, pounding on the cell door in a sudden rage."

JA20 is a transitional quip. The menu text is "'No, thanks.'". The display text is "'No offense,' you say, 'but I'll find my own way out, thanks.'"
The following quip is JA21.

JA21 is a quip. The display text is "'Fine, then,' Jacobs snarls, 'good luck getting past the guards, runt.' He turns on his heel and stalks out, leaving you alone with the other prisoners."

JA22 is a quip. The menu text is "'Sure, let's go.'". The display text is "'Smart kid,' Jacobs says, following you closely. You can hear the other prisoner shouting something behind you, but soon their voices fade as you hurry down the corridor, leaving the cells far behind you.[paragraph break]Jacobs leads you down dim, torchlit halls until you reach a wooden door. Jacobs motions you to be silent, then puts his ear up to the wood. After a moment he nods, opens the door, and then shoves you through it into the next room.[paragraph break]Bright lantern-light blinds you, and when your eyes clear you see a dozen men of the Lord's Guard standing in a semicircle around you... and in the middle, the man in the red robes.[paragraph break]'Little mouse...' murmurs the man in the red robes, '...always finding some new hole to crawl through.'[paragraph break]Behind you, Jacobs puts his heavy hand on your shoulder and grips it tight. 'Like I said, runt,' he laughs, 'Fossville has taken a special interest in you. And aiding the Baron in his interests can be very profitable.'[paragraph break]The red-robed man and the guards close in on you. This time, you do not escape."

JA23 is a quip. The display text is "Jacobs snorts. 'You must be dim, you pathetic boozer.' To you he says, 'We don't have time for him. I can take care of the guards; he can barely unlace his breeches to take a leak. If you want to do the smart thing, then let's go now.' And he jerks his thumb toward the east passage."

