Chapter 6 - Earl of Bresa

The Earl of Bresa is a male ballgoer. The description of the Earl of Bresa is "The Earl of Bresa has a bald head and a huge, curly, red beard. His lavish, colorful clothes are stained with wine and food. He laughs too loudly and has a habit of putting his greasy fingers on other guests — usually a friendly slap on the back for the men, elsewhere for the women. Despite Jacobs['] warning, you find yourself liking him immediately." Understand "man" as the Earl of Bresa.

The distant description of the Earl of Bresa is "The Earl is easy to spot from anywhere in the room: he's the one roaring with laughter and throwing fistfuls of money at the chamber orchestra, much to the guests['] amusement and the musicians['] embarassment."

Section 2 - Conversation 

Rule for initiating conversation with the Earl of Bresa:
	if BR1 is unfired,
		change the chosen opening gambit to BR1;
